## Pre-flight: API state at test start

At the moment this step began, GET /healthstack/services was returning 404 -- the Surface
auto-deploy watcher had not yet restarted Flask after the mw-backend push (consistent with
the warning in deploy.out). The watcher completed its restart within approximately 15s of
this step starting. All /healthstack/* endpoints returned 200 by the time the main Playwright
run executed.

Verified via curl before Playwright run:
  https://api.michaelwegter.com/health           -> 200 {"status":"ok","version":"1.0.0"}
  https://api.michaelwegter.com/healthstack/services -> 200 (4 providers JSON)
  https://api.michaelwegter.com/healthstack/login (POST patient) -> 200 (JWT + role=patient)

